The Big, Beautiful Bill provided significant support for Louisiana farmers, including through my Drought Assistance Improvement Act which was included in the bill. 

These reforms will strengthen disaster relief for livestock producers by allowing more timely payments for producers who suffer grazing losses due to drought.

Current law only allows one disaster payment after 8 consecutive weeks of severe drought. Moving forward, producers can receive one payment after 4 weeks and two payments after 8 weeks of severe drought.

SUPPORTING FAMILIES:

The One Big, Beautiful Bill supports families by expanding the Child Tax Credit and Adoption Tax Credit while providing more incentives for paid leave and childcare. 

- Permanently extends the doubled Child Tax Credit & provides an additional $400 for a family of four.

- Increases tax incentives for employers to offer childcare & paid leave.

- Makes the Adoption Tax Credit refundable.

- Expands the amount that families can contribute to pre-tax savings plans for childcare.

SUPPORTING LAW ENFORCEMENT AND OTHER OVERTIME WORKERS:

The One Big, Beautiful Bill eliminates taxes on up to $12,500 in annual overtime pay for hourly workers - including for many of our brave law enforcement officers.

NO TAXES ON TIPS:

The One Big, Beautiful Bill eliminates taxes on tips for waiters, waitresses, and other service workers. 

This tax cut will boost incomes by up to $1,300 annually for hardworking tipped workers.

The FARM Act would direct the Secretary of Agriculture to provide one-time economic assistance payments to farmers of qualifying commodities facing economic hardships. This support will help them sustain their operations and prepare for the upcoming harvest.

By improving access to financial resources, the bill ensures that assistance effectively reaches those who need it most.

As I’ve traveled across the Fifth District, I’ve heard directly from farmers who are on the verge of bankruptcy and desperately need targeted assistance in order to continue feeding our nation and fueling our economy.

This bill responds to the immediate needs of our agricultural community by providing targeted assistance so that our farmers are equipped to sustain their operations, support their families, and contribute to the local economy.
